The paper deals with information-theoretic security and privacy in the context of remote data storage and deletion. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, given the focus on privacy and security, cs.CR is the most likely category. The paper also involves the use of protocols and algorithms, which could place it in cs.IT and cs.CC. The mention of remote data storage and deletion suggests cs.DC, while the focus on privacy delegation could be relevant to cs.SE.
